 PVC  He said the distribution exercise, which commenced in the metropolis last Monday, was being conducted at designated Continuous Voters Registration (CVR) centres across the state.“We reassure our people that the commission is determined to provide a level playing ground,” he said. Ibrahim noted that a hitch-free PVCs distribution exercise would add value to democracy, regretting that insecurity to lives and property affected registration last year in Abadam, Marte, Kala/Balge and Guzamala councils.He said this informed the commission’s decision to convert most of the Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) camps into registration centres. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .